    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2090 <hi rend="superscript">9/14</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State (<persName
                            corresp="#p_WF1">White</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-22">August 22,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Argentine Ambassador called and showed me telegrams from his Government
                    indicating that it was pleased with the statement made by Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRW1">Bliss</persName> and on the basis thereof would take much
                    pleasure in supporting in La Paz the efforts of the Neutral Commission.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d272fn2">See telegram No. 78, August 19, 7 p.m., from the
                        Ambassador in Argentina, <ref target="#pg_186">p. 186</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EFA1">Espil</persName> said that his Embassy was now
                    decoding a long message from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SLC1">Saavedra
                        Lamas</persName> in which the latter was sending him the outline of a
                    proposal which he has in mind for supplementing and extending the Kellogg-Briand
                        Pact.<note n="3" xml:id="d272fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1928v01#pg_153">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 153</ref>.</note> He was asking Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_EFA1">Espil</persName>’s views regarding it and,
                    before anything is said to the United States, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SLC1"
                        >Saavedra Lamas</persName> will discuss the matter with the Brazilian,
                    Chilean and Peruvian Governments. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EFA1"
                        >Espil</persName> said he would let me know more about it when it is
                    deciphered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WF1">F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] W[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">hite</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
